			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">nccopycode.c's SerializeAllProcessors() gratuitously maps a page as PROT_READ|PROT_WRITE|PROT_EXEC (or the Windows equivalent, PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE).

RWX mappings are considered dangerous because they make it easier to successfully exploit memory safety bugs.

I noticed this while investigating issue 1994.  This issue can cause the size of the RWX mapping to grow to multiple pages on Mac OS X.
